ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 1575 Page 1
1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3500 of Title 56, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The Department of Human Services shall conduct a feasibility
5 study on the potential establishment of a unified and streamlined
6 eligibility and enrollment system for public assistance programs
7 administered by the state that would promote efficiency,
8 accessibility, and coordination of services across programs
9 including, but not limited to:
10 1. The Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP);
11 2. The Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF) program;
12 3. Child care subsidies;
13 4. The Low Income Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP);
14 5. The state Medicaid program; and
15 6. The Women, Infants, and Children (WIC) program.
16 B. As part of the feasibility study, the Department shall issue
17 a request for information on a unified and streamlined eligibility
18 and enrollment system to gather information about potential vendors
19 and their capabilities and to ascertain an estimate of the initial
20 and ongoing costs of the system.
21 C. The Department of Human Services, the Oklahoma Health Care
22 Authority, and the State Department of Health shall coordinate to
23 conduct the feasibility study.
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 1575 Page 2
1 D. At the conclusion of the feasibility study, the Department
2 of Human Services shall electronically submit a report to the
3 President Pro Tempore of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of
4 Representatives, and the Governor that summarizes the findings of
5 the feasibility study including, but not limited to, information
6 obtained through the request for information required under
7 subsection B of this section and cost estimates of the unified and
8 streamlined eligibility and enrollment system.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
10 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
11 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
12 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
13 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.”
